@NODE NODE_INTR "Introduction"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Introduction@{UB}

Audithec is a simple program to collect your Audio Compact Disk collection!
I'm using it for my 200+ CD.

Newest archives are protected by digital signature PGP.
You can download "PGP 5.1" for AmigaOS in many WEB pages; i found it here:
"http://www.mirrors.wiretapped.net/security/cryptography/apps/pgp/PGP/5.0/amiga/"

My PGP key is here:
"http://digilander.libero.it/enzobarba/"
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_REQUIR "System requirements"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Requirements@{UB}

* Any Amiga with at least OS 3.1 and some Mb of RAM

* @{"MUI" link NODE_MUI} 3.8+ with the default Classes

* @{"NList.mcc" link NODE_MUI}         v.19+  NList Open Source Team, (Gilles Masson)

* @{"NListView.mcc" link NODE_MUI}     v.19+  NList Open Source Team, (Gilles Masson)


If appears the requester "OpenWindow() failed" check this libraries and their versions.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_INST "Installation"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Installation@{UB}
Any installer-script is provided.
In the main archive you can find the true archive and my PGP signature to check it.
My PGP key is on my @{"WEB pages" link NODE_ME}.


type in shell:

Lha -x x <your_path>/Audithec.lha RAM:
cd RAM:
Lha -x x Audithec102.lha RAM:
cd RAM:Audithec
Copy Audithec ../your_path/
Copy Audithec.info ../your_path/
Copy catalogs/<your_language_dir>/Audithec.catalog Locale:catalogs/<your_language_dir>/
Copy Docs/Audithec.guide HELP:

NOTE:
libraries and classes names are CASE-SENSITIVE
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_FEAT "Features"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Features@{UB}

* FREEWARE. No requesters and no expiry date;

* Fully @{"Localized" link NODE_LOCAL}

* Search, Image-Attach and some basic functions;

* Export to CSV-;  CSV-TAB  AmigaGuide;

* Shortcuts for all the functions;

* (This) HELP on line;

* MUI-GUI;
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_USAGE "Usage"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Usage@{UB}

Audithec is very easy to use.

New                    Reset and open a new database
Load                   Load a database from a file
Save                   Save the current database
Save As                Save the current database and ask you for a new file-name
                       (Audithec save current database in both 'name.cd' and 'name.cd.bk':
                       'name.cd.bk' is older)

Export CD              Export the CD only of the database to an ASCII-file
Export Song            Export the Songs only of the database to an ASCII-file
Export All             Export all the database (CD and Songs) to an ASCII-file

                       Audithec exports the whole archive by following the listview's order.
                       i.e.: if you want to save the list ordered by authors
                            1. open the listview with the checkmark
                            2. put in alphabetical order the list by clicking
                               on the title of the third column
                            3. choose the export type (Export xx)


Export to (cycle)      With this gadget you can select the format for the output file:
                       you can use 'CSV-TAB', 'CSV-dot and comma' and AmigaGuide format.
                       Both formats CSV-xx could be imported from TurboCalc® or MSExcel®.
                       In AmigaGuide format Audithec automatically make a list ordered
                       by 'ID' then by 'Titles' and last by 'Authors'.


List (checkmark)       Show/Hide the global-listview
Song list (checkmark)  Show/Hide the song-listview
Find                   Show/Hide the Search options


Show                   Show the attached image at the current record
                       (Audithec search for "SYS:Utilities/multiview" to show the file)

(button near 'Show')   Set the attached image for the current record


Add song               Open a window to add new songs
Delete song            Delete the selected entry in song-listview
(song-listview)        By double-clicking on entry you can modify it


First                  Show the first record in the database
Previous               Show the previous record in the database
Go to  %n              Move to record number %n
Next                   Show the next record in the database
Last                   Show the last record in the database
Add                    Open a window to add a new CD-record
Modify                 Open a window to modify an existing CD-record (current)
Delete                 Delete the current record


Refresh                Copy the content of the database in the global listview
(Search checkmark)     Set the fields to search in
Find                   Start the research
Find next              Continue the research
Cancel                 Break research and return to main window

See @{"Notes" link NODE_NOTE} section too.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_NOTE "Notes"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Notes@{UB}

FILE:     Audithec saves the database in a file ASCII with a simple structure;
          this file COULD be edited, but DON'T edit it by hand:
          you may cause crash, faulty data or data loss in database.

          Anyhow, if you have a problem with the data-file, you could send it to me
          and i will try to repair it.


STACK:    Audithec, like almost all MUI-programs, needs bigger stack value.
          I see that it uses until 8K with a medium database: set it to 16K should
          be safer in every way.


ID field: -is read-only;
          -is written only when you add a record, in progressive mode
          -can be overwritten only if you delete the record
          -if you delete a record, i.e. number 6, you will see a 'hole'
           among the record number 5 and 7
          -in the field 'Number of records: num/tot' the value 'num' will be progressive
           (without 'holes')
          -each 'hole' will be displayed within the slider in the 'Add' window
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_LOCAL "Translation of Audithec"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Translation of Audithec@{UB}

Audithec supports locale.library.

In the archive (Audithec/catalogs/) you can find the files

  Audithec.cd v2.2
  Audithec.catalog (italian) v2.2
  Audithec.ct      (italian) v2.2


If you would translate Audithec to other languages you can upload the
translation's files on Aminet or send them to me: i'll include them in the
archive.
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_BUGS "BUGS"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}Bugs@{UB}

None ..at this moment!

If you find a bug please send me an Email with the subject "Audithec bug"
and your configuration



I tested this program on:
* A4000, CyberStormMKIII 060/50, 128Mb RAM, CVisionPPC, OS 3.9,
  HD9.1Gb ATLAS SCSI-UW, HD80Gb Maxtor IDE, HP LaserJet 1200,
  HP ScanJet II SCSI, Yamaha CDRW 16-10-40 SCSI, CD-ROM 48x


and:
* WinUAE with OS 3.9
@ENDNODE


@NODE NODE_HIST "History"

@{LINDENT 3}
@{B}History@{UB}
1.0.3 (2006-Aug-02)
      Added: Export to AmigaGuide format
      Fixed: some minor bugs

1.0.2 (11-Oct-2005)
      Fixed: Load->Cancel don't refresh current record
      Added: gauge for load-save-free operations
      Added: now Audithec saves the checkmark's status too (not search options)
      Added: Hungarian catalog (thanks to D¾sa Mßrton <dm_@freemail.hu>)
      Change: speed improve during loading

1.0.1 (12-Jul-2005)
      Fixed: possible crashes with longer strings
      Fixed: Audithec saves wrong databases in MOS
      Change: now Audithec exports the list ordered
      Change: new layout of exported files
      Change: updated catalog
      Change: removed 'Refresh' button
      Added: by double-clicking on listview's entry opens modify window
      Added: Exports the database in 'CSV-TAB' or 'CSV-dot and comma' format
      Others changes and corrections

1.0   First public release. (18-Jun-2005)
@ENDNODE


